Family members on Saturday grieved for their

slain loved ones and criticized the security arrangements at the Royal Marines Music School, where an IRA terrorist attack killed 10 military musicians.
Jean Cleatheroe, whose son Andrew was killed, joined local residents and opposition politicians in denouncing the use of private security firms to protect the music school and 29 other military establishments in Britain.
We have always said how easy it would be for anyone to get in ... What could ordinary security men do to stop terrorists?"
"I'm proud of my uniform and I'm proud of all the Marines I knew.
